CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, pg. 27 reads: "He Won A Bowling Trophy, Presented Another - William (Andy) Anderson, captain of the Courier Bowling team at the Hillvue Alleys, won the championship crown for himself in Men's Singles Classic League and the Courier team, which he heads, won the fifth place team trophy, donated by the Steel City League. In the photo at the left, Mr. Anderson presents the team trophy to Courier publisher, Mrs. Robert L. Vann, ... There were ten teams in the league.  Other members of the Courier team not shown were Harry Gladden, William Smith, Walter Smith and William Price. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Vann and William "Andy" Anderson, holding fifth place team trophy won by the Courier bowling team, Steel City League, posed in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper office
